      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Digitoxigenin is a heart stimulant obtained from the purple foxglove <i>Digitalis purpurea</i> and used in the treatment of heart disease. Draw the three-dimensional conformation of digitoxigenin, and identify the two –OH groups as axial or equatorial.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbTBZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c41b413ff63ffffd68b26cdfbfcef02e800b64ae/OChem_27_EC_018.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of digitoxigenin. It is a beta-hydroxy steroid with one wedged hydroxyl and two wedged methyls at the ring juctions,and substituted furanone\">",
